{
  "texts": [
    "As medical practices evolve and new diseases or treatments emerge, models that are not retrained may produce inaccurate results, a problem seen in other AI applications in healthcare.",
    "23 Another limitation concerns the ethical considerations of using AI in clinical settings.",
    "24 As the model automates decision-making, it introduces a risk of \"black box\" decision-making 25, where the reasoning behind coding choices is not transparent to clinicians and payers.",
    "The most problematic here would be systematic errors that can't be identified over coding.",
    "This is much harder to trace when it's a \"black box\" model."
  ]
}